    <h1>Privacy Policy for Fanvas</h1>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> [Insert Date]</p>
    <p>At Fanvas, we respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding information collection, stating clearly that we do not collect, store, or share any personal data from our users.</p>
    <h2>Information We Do Not Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Fanvas does not collect or store any personally identifiable information, such as names, email addresses, or contact details.</li>
        <li><strong>Image Data:</strong> Images you upload for analysis are processed temporarily and are not stored on our servers. Once the analysis is complete, the images are immediately deleted.</li>
        <li><strong>Device Data:</strong> We do not collect any device-related information, including IP addresses, device identifiers, or other usage data.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>Since we do not collect any user data, there is no risk of your information being stored, processed, or shared with third parties.</p>
    <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p>Fanvas is safe for users of all ages, and we do not knowingly collect any data from users, including children under the age of 13.</p>
    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy if needed. Any updates will be effective immediately upon posting on this page.</p>
    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at fanvasapp11@gmail.com.</p>
